constructors.comment: Construct a new vector with the specified values.

all.name: all
all.comment: Splat vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.Vector2-all.value into all lanes of the vector.

min.name: min
min.comment: Set the values of vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.min.result to the minimum of vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.min.a and vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.min.b for each line.

max.name: max
max.comment: Set the values of vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.max.result to the maximum of vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.max.a and vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.max.b for each line.

setFrom.name: setFrom
setFrom.comment: Set the values by copying them from vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.setFrom.other.

splat.name: splat
splat.comment: Splat vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.splat.arg into all lanes of the vector.

normalizeLength.name: normalizeLength
normalizeLength.comment: Normalize this. Returns length of vector before normalization.

postmultiply.name: postmultiply
postmultiply.comment: Transforms this into the product of this as a row vector, postmultiplied by matrix, vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.postmultiply.arg. If vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.postmultiply.arg is a rotation matrix, this is a computational shortcut for applying, the inverse of the transformation.

scaleOrthogonalInto.name: scaleOrthogonalInto
scaleOrthogonalInto.comment: Rotate this by 90 degrees then scale it. Store result in vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.scaleOrthogonalInto.out. Return vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.scaleOrthogonalInto.out.

multiply.name: multiply
multiply.comment: Multiply entries in this with entries in vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.multiply.arg.

divide.name: divide
divide.comment: Divide entries in this with entries in vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.divide.arg.

copyFromArray.name: copyFromArray
copyFromArray.comment: Copies elements from vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.copyFromArray.array into this starting at vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.copyFromArray.offset.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of vector_math/vector_math.Vector2.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.
